than humiliation,

00:42:53.640 --> 00:42:57.730
especially if you
personally feel that way.

00:42:57.730 --> 00:43:01.650
And so the philosophy
of my program

00:43:01.650 --> 00:43:05.440
is that you work until
you get it right.

00:43:05.440 --> 00:43:07.450
So I don't actually
even grade until you

00:43:07.450 --> 00:43:11.550
get an A. Kids will revise
things over and over and over.

00:43:11.550 --> 00:43:13.660
I have a mastery-based system.

00:43:13.660 --> 00:43:15.950
So you can revise-- you
come into the program,

00:43:15.950 --> 00:43:19.030
you don't know how
to write, so then you

00:43:19.030 --> 00:43:23.310
revise that essay or
that article 10 times.

00:43:23.310 --> 00:43:25.860
And in between each
revision, there is no grade.

00:43:25.860 --> 00:43:27.930
You only get the
grade at the end.

00:43:27.930 --> 00:43:31.630
And so I think kids need
to be given a freedom,

00:43:31.630 --> 00:43:33.000
freedom like that to fail.

00:43:33.000 --> 00:43:34.920
But what happens in
a lot of the programs

00:43:34.920 --> 00:43:37.092
is that you get a
grade, and then they

00:43:37.092 --> 00:43:38.716
average that grade
with the other grade

00:43:38.716 --> 00:43:40.674
and then they average
the other one at the end.

00:43:40.674 --> 00:43:44.790
You know, you can get 89.4
and you get a B, B plus.

00:43:44.790 --> 00:43:47.890
And then your parents
get mad and whatever.

00:43:47.890 --> 00:43:51.240
So I think there needs to
be less emphasis on grades,

00:43:51.240 --> 00:43:54.380
more emphasis on it's
OK to make a mistake.

00:43:54.380 --> 00:43:56.460
It's OK to be a kid.

00:43:56.460 --> 00:44:00.700
